<p>My <code>LogOff</code> action only works for the first session - other sessions from other browsers on same computer can not log out. </p>  <p>Also, the <code>LogOff</code> action is not called when the request has been cached by server. </p>  <p>This is my <code>LogOff</code> action:</p>  <pre><code>[HttpPost] [ValidateAntiForgeryToken] public ActionResult LogOff() {     MvcAuthentication.Models.ConfirmList.Remove();     AuthenticationManager.SignOut(DefaultAuthenticationTypes.ApplicationCookie);     return RedirectToAction("Index", "Home"); } </code></pre>  <p>What would be preventing other browser session from logging off?</p>